::KitKat::

She lowered her head, she was getting tired and breathing felt like a 
strain. "NO,  not all of us go.  Send a flier to check the base out.  
The maximals may still have an eye on the base seeing if we might 
come back.  One bot go to scout around the old base, then report 
back.  Another flier go and look for another base."  She stopped and 
had to catch her breath.  She coughed and whimpered.  "Then go 
and..and.." She groaned as her ribs ached in protest of wanting to 
breath.  She broke out in a small sweat and shivered. She was having 
trouble breathing.  "then go and find a place for us to hole up for 
the night.  We will look for a new base in the morning."  She coughed 
and groaned.
